Description: CVE-2026-6253 - Clear proxy credentials on port or scheme change
 When following redirects that change the proxy port or scheme,
 the proxy credentials were not being cleared, potentially
 leaking credentials to unintended proxies. This adds
 Curl_reset_userpwd() and Curl_reset_proxypwd() helper functions
 and calls Curl_reset_proxypwd() unconditionally in the redirect
 handler to ensure proxy credentials are always reset to the
 configured option values on every redirect.
 .
